{
  "text": "is given by a linear function with slope −1, and we can write E 0 (R, p) − κ(C) = E 0 (R + κ(C), p). The second part of the bound under the maximum in (8) is the main result of [CITATION_1] , see Theorem 1 of that paper]. The above proof is a shorter way to obtain it.",
  "correct_citation": {
